-- 
Senegal Sugar Producer to Boost Output by 50%, Quotidien Says

-- B y   D r e w   H i n s h a w
-- 
2011-08-10T11:38:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/senegal-sugar-producer-to-boost-output-by-50-quotidien-says.html
Compagnie Sucriere Senegalaise , a
maker of sugar in the West African nation, will spend 70 billion
CFA francs ($152.6 million) to increase output by 50 percent,  le
Quotidien  reported, citing Human Resources Director El Hadji
Bachir Sall.  New sugar-cane processing plants will allow the company to
produce 150,000 metric tons of the sweetener each year, compared
with current rate of 100,000 tons, the Dakar-based newspaper
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Drew Hinshaw in Dakar via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 